commit.message:
[K/N][tests] Use swiftc optimization flags depending on K/N opt mode

Currently, Native test infra always invokes swiftc without any
optimization flags when compiling Swift sources (e.g. in
"FrameworkTest").

On the other hand, in production, "release" (aka "optimized") Kotlin
binaries are typically used in Release Xcode configurations, which
also enable optimizations for Swift code. Similar for Debug Xcode
configurations.

So it makes more sense to enable optimizations for Swift code in
tests whenever Kotlin code is compiled in optimized mode. This way,
the tests would be more aligned with production.

This commit does that, by adding optimization-related flags to swiftc
invocations in test infra, mimicking the flags Xcode passes by
default in corresponding configurations.

^KT-65436

tree 2b97884813bd63b13349e9087cb85039ae8f7ed8
